@let
  age int = 30
  name string
  gender = "f"
  alive = true
  progress float
@end

@testbed alpha
  age = 50
  name = "Bob"
  gender = "m"
@end

--- this is how comments look now

# start

This is the first beat. My age is {age}.

@if age > 30

I'm over 30!

@elseif age > 10

I'm over 10!

@else

I'm 10 or under!

@endif

~ age += 1  --- inline mutation

Another year! Now my age is {age}.

> Again!
  -> start
> Bye

EXIT
:call_method()

(? gender = "m") ~ age += 2 --- conditional operation


tester: This is an attributed beat.

> This choice will continue
> Goes to grandchild b
  -> .alice.b
> Goes to child2
  -> .bob

This is the continuation beat.

